metadata.name: Endless Ridge #98
metadata.description:
Generative scene programmed by GLSL, continuously changing its form with time.
Plenty of them maintain minimal with monotone,
some of them varied as light shined on them from time to time,
some of them are veiled with mist and clouds,
and few of them reflected silver light with special textures.

Minted one piece then you’ll own one view to observe.

Created by Natalie.J

metadata.name: Mosaic #835
metadata.description:
---
Notes:
- Click to pause/unpause
- The aspect ratio is fixed 1:1 because of the way the grid and movements are generated to make sure they're the same on all screens. 
---
Description:
An 80X80 grid of tiles are scrambled, shuffled, shifted, streamed, transported,
conveyed, moved, deposited. 

There are 15 initial tile states and 5 color palettes. A set of 12 unique motion patterns
are generated for each piece. 
---
Acknowledgements:
This piece is inspired by Kim Asendorf, whose pixel-level algorithms I'm
transfixed by, and Ksawery Komputery, whose algorithmic tile-works I'm crazy
about. 
---
Made by Sam Tsao (@sam___tsao) with P5.js 
December 2021, Germany

metadata.name: Muladhara #4
metadata.description: The Root Chakra (Muladhara) is the first. Its energy comes from the earth element and is associated with the body's survival, safety and grounding function. It is at the base of the Chakra system and establishes the expansions in your life.

metadata.name: Svadhishana #3
metadata.description: The Sacrum Chakra is the second from the bottom up, it is connected with our sexual, creative and emotional part. The Element of this Chakra is Water, as its energy is fluid and flexible. The Function of this Chakra is related to pleasure.

metadata.name: Manipura #1
metadata.description: This is a Chakra characterized by willpower, personal power and mental abilities. The energy of the third Chakra or Manipura in Sanskrit is moved when we are in tune with the universe.

metadata.name: anomalia.12 #22
metadata.description:
Each one of the creations are movements in search of irregularity. Sequential modulation of shapes with the oscillator causes a sense of depth. With the help of noise and voronoi, it was possible to simulate a kind of dance between the shapes. Made with Hydra library.

Full screen will provide you a better view of the elements.

humachine
humanized
experiment

São Paulo, Brasil. 25/Janeiro/2022
